HEADWORD: classified
<hw>classified</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>arranged into
classes or categories; <as>as, <ant>unclassified</ant></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> categorized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>assigned to a class of documents withheld from
general circulation; -- of information or documents. Opposite of
<ant>unclassified</ant>.</def> <note>[Narrower terms:
<stype>eyes-only</stype>; <stype>confidential</stype>;
<stype>restricted</stype>; <stype>secret</stype>;
<stype>sensitive</stype>; <stype>top-secret</stype>]</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

